Children of Time
Adrian Tchaikovsky
978000833147
A race for survival among the stars... Humanity's last survivors escaped earth's ruins to find a new home. But when they find it, can their desperation overcome its dangers? WHO WILL INHERIT THIS NEW EARTH?
The novel is praised for its imaginative scope, thought-provoking themes of humanity, religion, and civilization, and its masterful world-building. Some readers found the character development limited by the story's vast timescale.
4.3
